# OSS docs are customer-facing (`super/docs`)

`super/docs/` (Hugo site → https://super.docs.sconts.com/) is **public documentation for all customers and the community**.

## Do

- Document OSS `superd` / CLI behavior, config schema, public APIs, and subscription **product** concepts (license key, plugins directory, feature matrix) at a customer-safe level.
- Prefer links to the public docs site over dumping commercial process detail into OSS pages.

## Do not put in `super/docs/` (or other public OSS surfaces: `README.md`, `SECURITY.md`, public changelogs)

- Signing keys, key paths, or how to generate / rotate `private.key` / `public.key`
- Internal SOPs (`license-sop`, phase1-drill, ledger, Afdian / payment ops)
- Manager / gen_license / commercial CI secrets, repo-private runbooks
- Exact commercial packaging internals beyond “obtain the subscription plugin archive from your vendor”
- Customer-only endpoints that encourage bypassing auth
- Private GitHub URLs, tokens, or monorepo layout that exposes commercial toolchain details

Commercial / ops detail belongs in the private commercial repository (`super-pro`), not in OSS docs.
